England Bowled Out for 237 in Second One-Day Cricket Match Against India

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-10-17T12:24:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/england-bowled-out-for-237-in-second-one-day-cricket-match-against-india.html
England was bowled out for 237 in
the second one-day cricket international against  India  in Delhi,
 Kevin Pietersen  top-scoring with 46 runs.  England recovered from losing opening batsmen Alastair Cook
and Craig Kieswetter before a run had been scored. Vinay Kumar
got four wickets for India.  India won the opening match of the five-game series by 126
runs. The teams are also set to play one Twenty20 international.  India was winless on a tour of England this summer, being
swept in a four-match Test series and also losing a one-day
series 3-0 and a Twenty20 match.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  